headlines.description: — Domantas Sabonis scored 37 points, and had 13 assists and 10 rebounds, to help the Sacramento Kings to a roller-coaster 131-110 victory over the Detroit Pistons on Tuesday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Domantas Sabonis' 37 points leads Kings to wild 131-110 victory over Pistons

headlines.description: — Karl-Anthony Towns scored 23 of his 28 points in the first half and the Minnesota Timberwolves led from start to finish Tuesday night in a 113-92 win over the Orlando Magic.
headlines.shortLinkText: Towns, Timberwolves roll to 113-92 win over Magic

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — The New York Knicks are not only unbeaten with OG Anunoby, they are dominant when their new forward is on the floor.
headlines.shortLinkText: Anunoby scores 23, Knicks improve to 5-0 with the forward by routing Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Desmond Bane scored 32 points to lead the injury-riddled Memphis Grizzlies to a 120-103 win over the Dallas Mavericks on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bane scores 32 to help injury-riddled Grizzlies beat the Mavericks 120-103

events.name: Toronto Raptors at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Toronto coach Darko Rajakovic went on a furious, table-pounding tirade against the officiating after the Los Angeles Lakers shot 23 free throws in the fourth quarter of a 132-131 win over the Raptors on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Toronto coach pounds table, rips officials after Lakers hold off Raptors 132-131 behind Davis' 41
